---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Marketing Apps for Backorders in 2026';
const description = 'A practical shortlist of Shopify email apps for backorder notifications, inventory events, customer expectations, and suppression.';
const apps = [['Klaviyo','Catalogs with detailed inventory behavior','Useful for product interest, waitlists, purchase, and customer-state segments.','Inventory freshness and suppression require strong event design.','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/marketing-automation'],['Omnisend','Commerce teams coordinating restock journeys','A practical fit for inventory alerts, product flows, and SMS coordination.','Inventory and promotional messages can collide.','https://www.omnisend.com/features/automations/'],['Sequenzy','Focused backorder communication','Good for concise status updates and a useful alternative-product path.','Backorder event integrations should be confirmed.','https://sequenzy.com/'],['Brevo','Broad transactional and marketing operations','Useful when status and lifecycle messages share a platform.','Traffic separation and product-state mapping need care.','https://www.brevo.com/features/transactional-email/'],['Shopify Email','Simple inventory announcements','A native starting point for basic availability communication.','Less suited to real-time backorder state.','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing']];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email marketing apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">Backorder email is a service promise. Customers need to know what they ordered, when it is expected, what can change, and how to get help.</p><p>Prioritize event freshness and accuracy over promotional features. Measure cancellation, refund, support, delivery-on-time, and alternative-product acceptance rates, and stop reminders when the order is fulfilled or cancelled.</p><h2>Shortlist at a glance</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>Strength</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[2]}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for backorders</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[2]}</p><p><strong>Why it stands out:</strong> {a[0]} is a candidate when it can maintain a clean distinction between an operational backorder notice and a marketing reminder. Provide a current estimate, make changes visible, and offer an alternative only when it genuinely fits. Customers should never have to parse promotional copy to find the status of a paid order.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros</th><td>{a[2]}</td></tr><tr><th>Cons</th><td>{a[3]}</td></tr><tr><th>Pricing context</th><td>Review current contacts, transactional sends, automation, and inventory integrations; every backordered line can create additional status events.</td></tr><tr><th>Source</th><td><a href={a[4]} rel="nofollow">Official product information</a></td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Priority</th><th>Prioritize</th><th>Measure</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Accuracy</td><td>Fresh inventory and order events</td><td>Support contacts</td></tr><tr><td>Choice</td><td>Alternative-product logic</td><td>Alternative acceptance</td></tr><tr><td>Trust</td><td>Clear status and suppression</td><td>Cancellations and refunds</td></tr></tbody></table><p>Read <a href="/alternatives">Shopify alternatives</a>, explore <a href="/use-cases/back-in-stock">inventory use cases</a>, or browse <a href="/apps">all Shopify email apps</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
